European Stocks, U.S. Futures Gain; Nokia, Continental Rise, Porsche Falls

-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 
2011-03-28T08:17:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/european-stocks-erase-loss-porsche-drops-on-share-sale-continental-gains.html
European stocks and U.S. index
futures advanced as technology companies gained, offsetting
carmakers, which declined. Asian shares retreated.  Nokia Oyj paced advancing shares, rising 2.2 percent, after
Goldman Sachs Group Inc. recommended buying the stock. Porsche
SE slumped 3 percent after the sports-car maker said it will
start a 5 billion-euro ($7 billion) share sale this week to
reduce debt. Continental AG rose 0.9 percent after  Schaeffler
Group  sold 1.8 billion euros of the tiremaker’s shares.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index rose 0.2 percent to 276.62 at
9:16 a.m. in  London , extending last week’s 3.1 percent rally.
The MSCI Asia Pacific Index lost 0.4 percent, while futures
contracts on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index expiring in June
advanced 0.2 percent to 1,313.5.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
 whadfield@bloomberg.net  